@dschwen Yeah it seems maybe we should have asked you for more :)
Anyway, just so I understand things, the AbaqusUMATMaterial declares a Jacobian_mult property, which gets consumed by StressDivergence and GeneralizedPlaneStrainOffDiag kernels (and probably more). Does it make sense for GeneralizedPlaneStrainUserObject to also use this property? Right now it uses the elasticity tensor but there are a number of occasions (here and here) where the Jacobian_mult property is set equal to the elasticity tensor.
Guess I'm just looking for the easy way out. Besides, the GeneralizedPlaneStrainUserObject only needs a single entry from the elasticity tensor to compute the Jacobian. Seems a bit overkill to create a new class just to get at a single value. I could be way off base here, so please let me know if I'm misunderstanding things.

